                      <span>2004-07-19</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book was first published in 1938!!!!!!! The fact that it contains some outdated notions about body image and fashion should come as no surprise.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A Perfect Book of Beauty</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      /
                      <span>3</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-05-30</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I think this book benefits already fashionable and charming people, rather than people who are in dire need of fashion or charm techniques. This book puts common sense and style together, which magazines and designers have yet figured out to do. I try to read the book every season, before shopping, in order to wash out all the nonsensical things magazines and designers like to tell you. Like 800 ways to make a Man Look at You!! OR Clothes, that make you stop Eating!!<P>This book makes you take a step back and re-evaluate your style choices. The best fashion book. Test of Time.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Vintage Gem</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
